      • conceptFromObjects

        public Concept conceptFromObjects(java.util.Collection<java.lang.Comparable> objects)
                           throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Returns the least concept that contains all objects contained in objects.

        Returns the concept that contains the common attributes of the objects contained in objects and their common objects, but no other objects or attributes.

        More formally, returns the concept (object'', object').

        Specified by:

      • edgeIterator

        public java.util.Iterator<Edge> edgeIterator(Traversal trav)
        Returns an iterator over all edges of this lattice. More formally, returns an iterator over all pairs of concepts, that are neighbors of each other.

        The order in which the edges (pairs of upper and lower neighbors) are returned depends on the trav argument.

        A top-down-breadth-first traversal guarantees that all edges having the same upper neighbor will be returned consecutively. However, there are no guarantees concerning the order in which the edges having the same upper neighbor are returned. Similarly, a bottom-up-breadth-first traversal guarantees that all edges having the same lower neighbor will be returned consecutively but there are no guarantees concerning the order in which the edges having the same lower neighbor are returned.

        Specified by:
        edgeIterator in interface Lattice
        Parameters:
        trav - the desired traversal.
        Returns:
        an iterator over all edges of this lattice.

      • violationIterator

        public java.util.Iterator<Edge> violationIterator(int supp,
                                         float conf,
                                         int diff)
        Returns an iterator over pairs of neighboring concepts that are similar to each other. How similar they have to be in order to be returned by this iterator is specified by the three arguments supp, conf and diff.
        Specified by:
        violationIterator in interface Lattice
        Parameters:
        supp - the minimal support, i.e. the minimal number of objects contained in the lower neighbor.
        conf - the minimal confidence, i.e. the minimal fraction l/u, where l is the number of objects in the lower neighbor and u is the number of objects in the upper neighbor. Must be a value between 0 and 1.
        diff - the maximal difference between the number of attributes in the lower neighbor and the number of attributes in the upper neighbor.
        Returns:
        an iterator over pairs of similar neighboring concepts.
